#: ../../source/solving.rst:116
msgid "DAE Mode Simulation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/solving.rst:118
msgid ""
"Beside the default ODE simulation, OpenModelica is able to simulate "
"models in `DAE mode`. The `DAE mode` is enabled by the flag "
":ref:`--daeMode <omcflag-daeMode>`. In general the whole equation system "
"of a model is passed to the DAE integrator, including all algebraic "
"loops. This reduces the amount of work that needs to be done in the post "
"optimization phase of the OpenModelica backend. Thus models with large "
"algebraic loops might compile faster in `DAE mode`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/solving.rst:125
msgid ""
"Once a model is compiled in `DAE mode` the simulation can be only "
"performed with :ref:`SUNDIALS/IDA <sundials_ida>` integrator and with "
"enabled :ref:`-daeMode <simflag-daeMode>` simulation flag. Both are "
"enabled automatically by default, when a simulation run is started."
msgstr ""

